  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 160&deg;C/ 140&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>cherry&nbsp;tomatoes</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and&nbsp;<strong>red wine vinegar</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray, with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and&nbsp;a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle them with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>&nbsp;and put the tray in the oven for 35-40 min or until the tomatoes start to&nbsp;wrinkle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> roughly into bite-size&nbsp;pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>baby kale</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds</strong>&nbsp;to a large bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pick the <strong>mint</strong>, <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>parsley</strong> leaves from their stems and add the <strong>leaves</strong> to the&nbsp;bowl - this is your<strong> herby salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>Set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/938.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>potatoes</strong>&nbsp;and leave&nbsp;them to steam dry&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mash them until smooth</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>curry powder</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>ground cumin</strong> and 2-3 tbsp<strong> olive oil</strong> and season generously with both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;then give everything a good mix up&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
